b:["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-1 flex-col overflow-hidden","children":[["$","$L13",null,{"title":"Components / Thinking Dots"}],["$","main",null,{"className":"flex-1 overflow-y-auto p-8","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl space-y-10","children":[["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-900","children":"Thinking Dots"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-500","children":"A lightweight 3×3 dot-grid loading indicator for agent thinking states. A single virtual gravity point travels through the grid on a pattern-defined path. Lines arc as quadratic Bézier curves pulled toward the gravity point, then relax back to straight as it moves away. Dots brighten and sweep through a spatial rainbow — colour determined by the angle from the gravity point to each dot — creating concentric colour rings that travel with the gravity point. Designed to sit inline with text or float independently."}]]}],["$","section",null,{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-base font-semibold text-zinc-800 mb-3","children":"Animation Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-zinc-500 mb-3","children":["Each pattern defines the path of the virtual gravity point across the grid.",["$","code",null,{"children":" breathe"}]," traces a rectangle perimeter (TL→TR→BR→BL);",["$","code",null,{"children":" breathe-x"}]," traces X-shaped diagonals (TL→BR→TR→BL). Both alternate push and pull on consecutive laps — the grid expands outward on the first half of each cycle, then contracts inward on the second."]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4","children":[["$","$L14","diagonal",{"label":"pattern=\"diagonal\"","children":["$","$L15",null,{"pattern":"diagonal","size":"md"}]}],["$","$L14","radial",{"label":"pattern=\"radial\"","children":["$","$L15",null,{"pattern":"radial","size":"md"}]}],["$","$L14","radial-pull",{"label":"pattern=\"radial-pull\"","children":["$","$L15",null,{"pattern":"radial-pull","size":"md"}]}],["$","$L14","horizontal",{"label":"pattern=\"horizontal\"","children":["$","$L15",null,{"pattern":"horizontal","size":"md"}]}],["$","$L14","random",{"label":"pattern=\"random\"","children":["$","$L15",null,{"pattern":"random","size":"md"}]}],["$","$L14","breathe",{"label":"pattern=\"breathe\"","children":["$","$L15",null,{"pattern":"breathe","size":"md"}]}],["$","$L14","breathe-x",{"label":"pattern=\"breathe-x\"","children":["$","$L15",null,{"pattern":"breathe-x","size":"md"}]}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-base font-semibold text-zinc-800 mb-3","children":"Colour Sweep"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-zinc-500 mb-3","children":"Colour is determined spatially by the angle from the gravity point to each dot, creating concentric rainbow rings that rotate and travel with the gravity point. Dots are grey at rest; rainbow colour sweeps through each dot as the gravity point approaches, then fades back to grey as it recedes."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4","children":[["$","$L14","diagonal",{"label":"pattern=\"diagonal\" · size=\"lg\"","children":["$","$L15",null,{"pattern":"diagonal","size":"lg"}]}],["$","$L14","radial",{"label":"pattern=\"radial\" · size=\"lg\"","children":["$","$L15",null,{"pattern":"radial","size":"lg"}]}],["$","$L14","radial-pull",{"label":"pattern=\"radial-pull\" · size=\"lg\"","children":["$","$L15",null,{"pattern":"radial-pull","size":"lg"}]}],["$","$L14","horizontal",{"label":"pattern=\"horizontal\" · size=\"lg\"","children":["$","$L15",null,{"pattern":"horizontal","size":"lg"}]}],["$","$L14","random",{"label":"pattern=\"random\" · size=\"lg\"","children":["$","$L15",null,{"pattern":"random","size":"lg"}]}],["$","$L14","breathe",{"label":"pattern=\"breathe\" · size=\"lg\"","children":["$","$L15",null,{"pattern":"breathe","size":"lg"}]}],["$","$L14","breathe-x",{"label":"pattern=\"breathe-x\" · size=\"lg\"","children":["$","$L15",null,{"pattern":"breathe-x","size":"lg"}]}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-base font-semibold text-zinc-800 mb-3","children":"Line Bending"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-zinc-500 mb-3","children":"Lines animate as quadratic Bézier curves whose control points are displaced toward the moving gravity point. Displacement uses an inverse-distance pull with quadratic rim taper — lines near the gravity point arc strongly toward it, while distant lines stay straight. As the gravity point moves through the grid, it pulls the nearest lines into smooth curves that travel with it. Slower durations make the arcing motion more visible."}],"$L16"]}],"$L17","$L18","$L19","$L1a","$L1b","$L1c","$L1d","$L1e","$L1f","$L20","$L21"]}]}]]}]
